-- Burundi Revenue Increased 18% in February From Year Earlier
-- B y   D e s i r e   N i m u b o n a
-- 2012-03-02T16:23:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/burundi-revenue-increased-18-in-february-from-year-earlier.html
The Burundi Revenue Authority
collected 35.8 billion francs ($25 million) in February, 18
percent higher than a year earlier, it said.  Revenue in the first two months of the year reached 89.6
billion francs compared with 68.2 billion francs in the same
period last year, according to a statement distributed in the
capital, Bujumbura, today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Desire Nimubona in Bujumbura at 
 dnimubona@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  